  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But if you shall at all turn from following me, you or your children,.... From my worship, as the Targum; either Solomon or his successors, or the people of Israel and their posterity; should they turn their backs on God and his worship, meaning not in a single instance, or in some small degree; but as in the original, \"if in turning ye turn\" (e), that is, utterly, and entirely, or wholly turn from him and his worship to other gods, as follows: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and will not keep my commandments and my statutes, which I have set before you, but go and serve other gods, and worship them: neglecting the will and worship of God, go into idolatrous practices, as Solomon himself did. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(e)   \"si avertendo aversi fueritis\", Pagninus, Montanus, &c. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(e)   \"si avertendo aversi fueritis\", Pagninus, Montanus, &c. ",
            "children": []
